						               													<description>Do you want to save the world with the help of a colorful mix of characters from the past and the present? Do you want to have fun creating stories while learning about human rights? Then BARABAR is the game for you!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In BARABAR, the players will have to collaborate with each other and play with characters of important people who have achieved great things for mankind. They belong to 5 clans: activists, environmentalists, artists, ecologists, and entrepreneurs. You will have to create stories on how these characters will help to solve challenges, some of them real or some of them more science fiction. Have you ever thought how Martin Luther King could help in a zombie apocalypse?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;BARABAR is both competitive and collaborative, as well as educational. It can be played in a variety of different ways depending on how you want to do it. &amp;#10;Some of the rules make the game more didactic while others make it more competitive.&amp;#10;It is ideal to play with friends, ideally from 2 to 6 players. The game usually takes from 20 minutes to 1 hours.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
